#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:4
msgid "fish_config - start the web-based configuration interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:9
msgid ""
"fish_config [browse]\n"
"fish_config prompt (choose | list | save | show)\n"
"fish_config theme (choose | demo | dump | list | save | show)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:16
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:18
msgid "``fish_config`` is used to configure fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:20
msgid ""
"Without arguments or with the ``browse`` command it starts the web-based "
"configuration interface. The web interface allows you to view your "
"functions, variables and history, and to make changes to your prompt and "
"color configuration. It starts a local web server and opens a browser "
"window. When you are finished, close the browser window and press the Enter "
"key to terminate the configuration session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:22
msgid ""
"If the ``BROWSER`` environment variable is set, it will be used as the name "
"of the web browser to open instead of the system default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:24
msgid ""
"With the ``prompt`` command ``fish_config`` can be used to view and choose a "
"prompt from fish's sample prompts inside the terminal directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:26
msgid "Available subcommands for the ``prompt`` command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:28
msgid "``choose`` loads a sample prompt in the current session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:29
msgid "``list`` lists the names of the available sample prompts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:30
msgid ""
"``save`` saves the current prompt to a file (via :doc:`funcsave <funcsave>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:31
msgid "``show`` shows what the given sample prompts (or all) would look like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:33
msgid ""
"With the ``theme`` command ``fish_config`` can be used to view and choose a "
"theme (meaning a color scheme) inside the terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:35
msgid "Available subcommands for the ``theme`` command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:37
msgid "``choose`` loads a sample theme in the current session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:38
msgid "``demo`` displays some sample text in the current theme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:39
msgid "``dump`` prints the current theme in a loadable format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:40
msgid "``list`` lists the names of the available sample themes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:41
msgid ""
"``save`` saves the given theme to :ref:`universal variables <variables-"
"universal>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:42
msgid "``show`` shows what the given sample theme (or all) would look like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:44
msgid ""
"The themes are loaded from the theme directory shipped with fish or a "
"``themes`` directory in the fish configuration directory (typically ``~/."
"config/fish/themes``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:46
msgid "The **-h** or **--help** option displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:49
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:51
msgid ""
"``fish_config`` or ``fish_config browse`` opens a new web browser window and "
"allows you to configure certain fish settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:53
msgid "``fish_config prompt show`` demos the available sample prompts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:55
msgid ""
"``fish_config prompt choose disco`` makes the disco prompt the prompt for "
"the current session. This can also be used in :ref:`config.fish "
"<configuration>` to set the prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:57
msgid ""
"``fish_config prompt save`` saves the current prompt to an :ref:`autoloaded "
"<syntax-function-autoloading>` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_config.rst:59
msgid ""
"``fish_config prompt save default`` chooses the default prompt and saves it."
msgstr ""
